00:11.560 --> 00:20.900
your poetry, so let me just ask a couple questions about the, say, your
television writing. You've written for many television shows such as, I guess,

00:20.940 --> 00:29.560
Twilight Zone, Alfred Hitchcock, and so forth. Do you still do that, or is that
phase of your career over? No, I've had two things on this year. The Electric

00:29.560 --> 00:40.460
Grandmother, which was starring Maureen Stapleton. And it's been on twice now
since January, a one-hour show about a robot grandmother that raises children.

00:40.880 --> 00:51.440
And it turned out very well. I was very proud of it. And then another of my
scripts was Any Friend of Nicholas Nickleby's is a Friend of Mine, starring Fred

00:51.440 --> 01:01.080
Gwynne, playing the part of a false Charles Dickens, and this was based
