05:47.500 --> 05:55.300
determines, when the muse comes on you, what determines whether you write a
story, a poem, a play, an opera, or whatever? I haven't the faintest idea. It

05:55.300 --> 06:05.000
just knocks me over. Sometimes in the middle of writing a poem, I'll say, oh my,
this is too big for a poem. I may very well finish the poem, but then I sit down

06:05.000 --> 06:15.740
and turn it into a short story immediately. or on a rare occasion it turns into
a stage play or a novel. But that doesn't happen as often. Most of the time I

06:15.740 --> 06:30.320
work in the short form. But quite often you take the simplest idea and it
evolves from the poetry form into... Well, I was, for instance, I was driving

06:30.320 --> 06:43.660
around in England a few years ago and a chauffeur of our car was talking about
driving and the Irish and funerals Irish wakes and what have you and he told of

06:43.660 --> 06:54.860
this one wake of some friends of his in a small town in Ireland where an English
