thing in all your work that you'd like to be remembered for? Oh, I hope that

15:29.900 --> 15:42.320
something wicked this way comes and is still around. I think it's a universal
book, at least I hope it is. It deals with children and growing up and growing

15:42.320 --> 15:52.360
old and getting sick and dying, all the things that happened to all the people
in the history of the world. I hope the book won't age. That it would belong to

15:52.360 --> 16:02.820
no special time, but to all times. It's my favorite, and I love it because I
suppose I'm locked into it with my father. My father is the hero of the book. I

16:02.820 --> 16:11.740
didn't know that at the time I wrote it. One night I got up and wandered around
the house and picked up the book and started to reread it, and suddenly cried

16:11.740 --> 16:23.980
out, and tears burst through my eyes, and I realized that I'd written my father
into the book as Mr. Holloway, who was the hero of the entire structure. So

16:23.980 --> 16:35.320
that's one of the reasons why I love it. I hope it will have a little life after
I'm gone. Yeah, we're going to teach a fantasy class here next semester at the

16:35.320 --> 16:42.120
college, and that's one of the books we're going to teach. Oh, great. In fact,
